title: Hey, I'm Solvin' Here!
subtitle: Hey, I'm Solvin' Here!
shortDescription: When a middle-aged white man is murdered in New York, the team goes there based on Tribeca's belief that the serial killer they've been tracking is the culprit. No one's on board with her theory, but as the main character, she drives the plot.

title: License to Drill
subtitle: License to Drill
shortDescription: When a sultry woman convinces Geils to investigate whether her husband is having an affair, he dons his P.I. hat, which lands him in trouble. Think Chinatown, because that's where this story comes from.

title: If You See Something, Solve Something
shortDescription: A naked woman crawls out of a child's backpack and doesn't remember a thing. Why? She couldn't tell you. Tribeca helps her trace her steps while Geils and Tanner track down a murderer on the run from prison.

title: Germs of Endearment
subtitle: Germs of Endearment
shortDescription: When an outbreak of a lethal virus threatens to liquefy everyone in Los Angeles and perhaps the world, the team realizes this might be the season's serial killer's magnum opus.

title: Go Get 'Em, Tiger
subtitle: Go Get 'Em, Tiger
shortDescription: People are still solid, but Dr. Scholls turns up missing, and the serial killer is still on the loose. Meanwhile, Lt. Atkins has a beautiful outdoor wedding. Do the two converge? That would tie things up nicely in the end.

title: Crawl Space
shortDescription: Bob learns that Linda's parents are coming for a visit, he takes drastic measures to avoid having contact with them. While fixing a leak in the attic, he pretends to get stuck while investigating a series of Prohibition Era passageways.

title: The Belchies
subtitle: The Belchies
shortDescription: The kids hunt for treasure in an abandoned taffy factory, and Bob and Linda must find them before the factory's scheduled demolition.

title: Fort Night
subtitle: Fort Night
shortDescription: Tina, Gene and Louise are filled with the Halloween spirit and head out with their friends for a candy-fueled adventure. Things take a turn for the worse when the kids build a fort and find themselves held hostage by Millie.

title: Christmas in the Car
subtitle: Christmas in the Car
shortDescription: After Linda kills the tree, the Belchers must go out on Christmas to find a new one. When Bob cuts off a truck, they are forced to spend the holiday together in the car. Back at the Belcher home, Teddy gets stuck in the kids' Santa trap.

title: Slumber Party
subtitle: Slumber Party
shortDescription: When Linda realizes that Louise has never had a sleepover, she throws her a surprise slumber party, much to Louise's chagrin. After Louise's repeated attempts to escape are thwarted, she decides to sabotage the party.

title: Tina and the Real Ghost
subtitle: Tina and the Real Ghost
shortDescription: Tina begins an out-of-this-world romance with a ghost that is believed to be living in the Belcher's basement. And when Bob realizes that an in-house ghost may increase revenues, he too becomes a fan of the paranormal entity.

title: The Runway Club
subtitle: The Runway Club
shortDescription: The kids are sentenced to Saturday detention and will do anything it takes to leave early so they can attend the Cotton Candy Festival. Meanwhile, Bob and Linda believe that they are being scammed by a young girl at the restaurant.

title: Housetrap
subtitle: Housetrap
shortDescription: In True Belcher fashion, the family gets stuck in a terrible storm while taking care of a beach house in Craggy Neck. The storm is the least of their worries when they are forced to take shelter with the mysterious owner of the home.

title: Who Am I?
subtitle: Who Am I?
shortDescription: Ray believes he is having an identity crisis.

title: Robert Needs Money
subtitle: Robert Needs Money
shortDescription: Ray and Debra loan $1,000 to pressed Robert, then are surprised when he uses it to go to Las Vegas.

title: The Sigh
subtitle: The Sigh
shortDescription: Ray gives Debra exclusive use of their bathroom.

title: Sweet Charity
subtitle: Sweet Charity
shortDescription: Ray reluctantly agrees to do some charity work at a hospital after Debra signs him up, but he soon becomes a hit with the patients and starts spending more time there than at home, much to his wife's dismay.

title: Meeting the Parents
subtitle: Meeting the Parents
shortDescription: Amy's folks show up unexpectedly at their daughter's house on a Sunday morning, wanting to talk Amy out of marrying Robert. First, they are stunned to see Robert there. Then, Frank and Marie arrive. It doesn't take long for the parents to dislike one another.

title: The Plan
subtitle: The Plan
shortDescription: When Amy puts Robert in charge of writing the wedding invitation, Ray and Frank suggest he make a mess of the job to convince Amy that she should plan the wedding herself. Robert drafts an appalling mock invite and waits for Amy's reply, which is worse than he expected.

title: Sleepover at Peggy's
subtitle: Sleepover at Peggy's
shortDescription: Ray takes Ally to her friend's house for a sleepover and is mortified when the girl's mother pats his behind after he helps set up a tent. Ray finds out that the mother is the same one Ray had a nasty run-in with over some Frontier Girl cookies a year before.

title: Who's Next
subtitle: Who's Next
shortDescription: Debra and Ray pick out replacement spouses for each other and jealousy starts. Marie announces that Rose, the elderly lady next door, has passed away. Marie is upset because Rose is the woman she'd chosen for Frank if she hadn't died.

title: The Shower
subtitle: The Shower
shortDescription: Debra drinks too much at Amy's bridal shower and is too tipsy to drive. When she can't reach Ray, Debra takes a nap in her car with the keys in the ignition and is awakened by a police officer, who arrests her for drunk driving. When her license is suspended, Debra must rely on Marie.

title: Baggage
subtitle: Baggage
shortDescription: Ray and Debra wind up in a two-week standoff over a suitcase. Robert thinks Ray and Debra are insane, while Frank and Marie can easily relate. Ray's parents offer words of wisdom ... with Frank counseling Ray and Marie advising Debra on how to resolve their marital differences.

title: Robert's Wedding
subtitle: Robert's Wedding
shortDescription: Robert and Amy exchange vows in a classic Barone family wedding ceremony.

title: Fun with Debra
shortDescription: Debra convinces Ray to let her join him on the golf course after she (once again) realizes that they don't have fun together anymore. Let's just say, it wasn't all fun.
description: Debra convinces Ray to let her join him on the golf course after she (once again) realizes that they don't have fun together anymore. Let's just say, it wasn't all fun.<\/p>

title: Thank You Notes
subtitle: Thank You Notes
shortDescription: Marie instantly tries to get the upper hand in her relationship with her new daughter-in-law when Amy and Robert return from their honeymoon, but Debra steps in, determined to stop Marie's meddling once and for all, which horrifies the guys.

title: Home from School
subtitle: Home from School
shortDescription: When Michael stays home from school for two days in a row, Ray suspects he simply has homework he hasn't finished. Ray decides to apply tough love. When Michael is forced to watch Ray work, the boredom leads him to confide why he doesn't want to return to class.

title: The One With George Stephanopoulus
shortDescription: While the men attend a hockey game and end up at a hospital, the women spy on President Clinton's top aide, George Stephanopoulos, who lives across the street.  Rachel receives her first paycheck.
description: Joey and Chandler invite Ross to a hockey game for his birthday (which was seven months ago), but all he can think about is his ex-wife, Carol. At the game, Ross' nose gets broken by a flying puck, and the guys spend the evening in the emergency room. Meanwhile, Rachel tries to come to terms with her new lifestyle (i.e., poverty and independence) and spends the night talking about guys and life (mostly guys) with Monica and Phoebe.<\/p>

title: The One With The Bullies
shortDescription: Chandler and Joey are scared of two bullies. Phoebe meets her long-lost family members.
description: Two guys come into the coffeehouse and "bully" Chandler and Ross, telling them never to come back to Central Perk again. Ross and Chandler avoid the coffeehouse for awhile, but eventually decide to confront their fears and the two bullies. As all four guys get ready to "settle things" with their fists, two robbers try to run off with the watches and keys the combatants have laid aside. Their common pursuit of the thieves brings them together and the bullies agree "everything's cool." Phoebe (with Rachel and Joey) goes to her dad's house again, determined to meet him. She is chased back to the car by a tiny, yet ferocious, dog, and decides it's still not the "right" time to meet her dad. Driving away, she accidentally runs over the dog. The vet fixes him up and when Phoebe returns it, she meets her step-mother and learns that her dad also abandoned this family a few years back. The nice thing is, Phoebe and her half-brother meet and do a little sibling bonding. Meanwhile, Monica gets hooked on the stock market and loses all her savings (one hundred and twenty seven dollars). Totally broke, she has to take a job in a theme restaurant where the staff wears costumes and lip synchs to cheesy pop tunes.

title: And the Group Head
subtitle: And the Group Head
shortDescription: When Max and Caroline can't figure out how to use the new cappuccino maker they bought for their cupcake business, they take temporary side jobs as baristas at a coffee house to learn the ropes.

title: And the Cronuts
subtitle: And the Cronuts
shortDescription: When Max and Caroline start losing business to the new cronut craze (half-croissant, half-donut), they come up with their own trend: cake fries.

title: And the Piece of Sheet
subtitle: And the Piece of Sheet
shortDescription: Caroline buys Max a new bedding set and gives away the old sheets to charity without realizing they had sentimental value to her.

title: And the Girlfriend Experience
subtitle: And the Girlfriend Experience
shortDescription: Han asks Max and Caroline to convince a stripper to pretend to be his girlfriend when his mother visits from Korea.

title: And the Dumpster Sex
subtitle: And the Dumpster Sex
shortDescription: Deke takes Max to his place after a great first date, but his so-called home is nothing like she expected. Meanwhile, Caroline feels empowered and then scared after she has a shady-looking car towed from the front of the Cupcake window.

title: And the Icing on the Cake
subtitle: And the Icing on the Cake
shortDescription: When Deke invites Max's friends over to his dumpster house, Caroline learns a big secret about his background.

title: And the Married Man Sleepover
subtitle: And the Married Man Sleepover
shortDescription: Caroline asks Max and Deke to join on her dinner date at Nicholas' loft to make sure she doesn't do anything she might regret. Caroline and Max also treat themselves to very special hair appointments.

title: And the Near Death Experience
subtitle: And the Near Death Experience
shortDescription: Caroline goes into a tailspin and drags Max with her when Nicolas tells her that he is going to leave is wife for her.

title: Fantasy Baseball
subtitle: Fantasy Baseball
shortDescription: Steve tries to get into baseball to connect with Stan. Roger creates real life drama for Francine after her favorite soap opera is cancelled.

title: I Am The Jeans: The Gina Lavetti Story
subtitle: I Am The Jeans: The Gina Lavetti Story
shortDescription: Francine tries to be a better friend to one of Roger's personas who is selling her homemade jeans on TV. Stan and Steve swap eyebrows.

title: Stan & Francine & Connie & Ted
subtitle: Stan & Francine & Connie & Ted
shortDescription: Steve introduces Stan and Francine to Barry's parents and Steve regrets it. Roger goes blind.

title: Rabbit Ears
subtitle: Rabbit Ears
shortDescription: Stan gets obsessed with a 1960's television show after picking up a secondhand TV. Roger decides to live as a baby and the family cares for him.

title: Jeff and the Dank Ass Weed Factory
subtitle: Jeff and the Dank Ass Weed Factory
shortDescription: Jeff wins a tour through a mysterious weed factory and brings Stan along.

title: Lost Boys
subtitle: Lost Boys
shortDescription: Roger breaks up Steve's friendship with Snot, Barry & Toshi. Jeff realizes he has a flair for house flipping and gets Stan, Francine and Hayley involved.

title: Shark?!
subtitle: Shark?!
shortDescription: Stan has Roger pretend to be a shark to help Steve overcome his fears. Hayley's friend Danuta becomes romantically interested in Klaus.

title: The Long March
subtitle: The Long March
shortDescription: Hayley and Jeff move into a van and start living life on the open road. Francine and Steve are haunted by a rideshare driver that they rated poorly.

title: The Hall Monitor and the Lunch Lady
subtitle: The Hall Monitor and the Lunch Lady
shortDescription: Steve goes undercover as a school hall monitor. Roger and Stan go catatonic after witnessing a grisly escalator accident.

title: Wild Women Do
subtitle: Wild Women Do
shortDescription: Jeff is forced to take Francine out for a not-so-wild night on the town. Klaus forces Steve to watch his celebrity impressions.

title: An Irish Goodbye
subtitle: An Irish Goodbye
shortDescription: Francine helps Hayley take a break from their marriages. Stan and Jeff pretend to be frontiersmen.

title: Stompe Le Monde
subtitle: Stompe Le Monde
shortDescription: Stan buys the rights a Broadway show after inheriting money from a dead uncle.

title: Mom Sauce
subtitle: Mom Sauce
shortDescription: Steve's life is turned upside down when Snot gets rich after his mom starts selling a new dipping sauce. Klaus, Stan, Roger and Jeff become mall fashion show models.

title: Hamerican Dad!
subtitle: Hamerican Dad!
shortDescription: Stan reluctantly invites Roger into his ham club. Francine decides to scare Greg.

title: Demolition Daddy
subtitle: Demolition Daddy
shortDescription: Thanks to Roger, Snot discovers his dead father was a demolition derby driver. Hayley takes Steve on a road trip, so he can learn to drive.

title: Pride Before the Fail
subtitle: Pride Before the Fail
shortDescription: Roger tries to force Hayley into graduating from community college so he can move into her room. Klaus repairs Francine's car.

title: Enter Stanman
subtitle: Enter Stanman
shortDescription: Roger helps Stan enter Francine's dreams after he becomes insecure about their contents.

title: No Weddings and a Funeral
subtitle: No Weddings and a Funeral
shortDescription: Klaus leaves the family after one too many harassments. 15 years later, they reconnect for his funeral.

title: Eight Fires
subtitle: Eight Fires
shortDescription: Roger helps Francine with her terrible cooking by bringing her to a remote Patagonian island. Stan gets a nail in his head and can't speak.

title: The Hand that Rocks the Rogu
subtitle: The Hand that Rocks the Rogu
shortDescription: Steve babysits Roger's ex-tumor, Rogu, to prove to Francine that he's ready for the responsibility. Stan and Francine get into trouble in their respective clubs.

title: 100 Years A Solid Fool
shortDescription: While running an errand in Little Columbia, Stan is confronted by his hidden past.

shortDescription: Conan O'Brien becomes the first American late-night host to do a show in Cuba in more than 50 years.

title: Conan in Armenia
subtitle: Conan in Armenia
shortDescription: Conan is on the road again as he becomes the first American late-night host ever to do a show from Armenia. Joining Conan will be his longtime assistant Sona Movsesian, who is of Armenian descent.

title: Conan in Qatar
subtitle: Conan in Qatar
shortDescription: Mission CONAN:  CONAN in Qatar, featuring Conan O'Brien and First Lady Michelle Obama on their recent trip to visit U.S. troops stationed at the Al Udeid Air Base in Doha, Qatar.

title: Conan in Korea
subtitle: Conan in Korea
shortDescription: Conan heads to South Korea with The Walking Dead's Steven Yeun. After being welcomed by thousands of screaming fans, they explore various parts of the country, including the Korean Demilitarized Zone (DMZ) and the Joint Security Area (JSA).

title: Conan Without Borders: Berlin
subtitle: Conan Without Borders: Berlin
shortDescription: On his fifth international trip as host of Conan, Conan O'Brien experiences the wonders of historic Berlin, from racing down the autobahn to mastering "schuhplattler" and even visiting a dominatrix.

title: Conan Without Borders: Made in Mexico
subtitle: Conan Without Borders: Made in Mexico
shortDescription: Conan has decided to strike a positive note by heading to Mexico City, where he'll outsource his show by shooting his latest Conan Without Borders special with the help of an all-Mexican staff, crew, guests and studio audience.

title: Conan Without Borders: Israel
subtitle: Conan Without Borders: Israel
shortDescription: O'Brien visits Tel Aviv and Jerusalem among other locales.

title: Conan Without Borders: Haiti
subtitle: Conan Without Borders: Haiti
shortDescription: CONAN travels internationally for the eighth time in three years for CONAN Without Borders: Haiti. After hearing President Trump's disparaging remarks about Haiti, O'Brien immediately decided to announce his intentions to visit the island nation.

title: Conan Without Borders: Italy
subtitle: Conan Without Borders: Italy
shortDescription: O'Brien put a different spin on his usual travel shows bringing along fan favorite show staffer Jordan Schlansky.

title: Conan Without Borders: Japan
subtitle: Conan Without Borders: Japan
shortDescription: Conan travels to Japan to learn about the country's culture.

title: Conan Without Borders: Australia
subtitle: Conan Without Borders: Australia
shortDescription: Conan is back with another international adventure. On this show, we'll find Conan down under, where he learns how to speak like a native Aussie, survive the outback and play Australia Rules football.

title: Conan Without Borders: Greenland
subtitle: Conan Without Borders: Greenland
shortDescription: After President Trump's remarks about purchasing the Danish territory, Conan will take the show internationally for the twelfth time to help broker the deal.

title: Conan Without Borders: Ghana
subtitle: Conan Without Borders: Ghana
shortDescription: On this adventure to Ghana, Conan will be accompanied by actor and comedian Sam Richardson (Veep, Detroiters) whose family is from the African nation.  Richardson has the life experience to act as the perfect cultural attache.

title: January 29, 2020
shortDescription: Full Frontal busts the myth that there's a social media bias against conservatives, argues that the only thing scarier than coronavirus is the defunding of the CDC, and finds out why we let Iowa tell us who's going to be president.
description: Full Frontal busts the myth that there's a social media bias against conservatives, argues that the only thing scarier than coronavirus is the defunding of the CDC, and sends Allana Harkin to find out why the heck we let Iowa tell us who's going to be president.

title: February 5, 2020
subtitle: February 5, 2020
shortDescription: Full Frontal ponders this week's myriad failures of democracy, argues that the state of dental care in America could use a good check up, and bravely takes on the terrifying world of healthcare costs.

title: February 12, 2020
subtitle: February 12, 2020
shortDescription: Full Frontal watches from a safe distance as the president embarks on a revenge tour and highlights the new right-wing propaganda site targeting Gen-Z. Plus, Sam meets the MVPs of the impeachment trial.

title: March 4, 2020
subtitle: March 4, 2020
shortDescription: Full Frontal attempts to strong arm its way through the massive onslaught of topical news, including all things Super Tuesday! Plus, Sam uncovers the sins committed by Christian healthcare sharing ministries.

title: March 11, 2020
subtitle: March 11, 2020
shortDescription: Full Frontal covers the harmful side effects of COVID-19 and rates the nature of our current gig-based economy at 0 stars. Then Mike Rubens heads south to learn how Trump's border wall is definitely messing with Texas.

title: March 25, 2020
subtitle: March 25, 2020
shortDescription: From the socially-isolated comfort of the woods in her backyard, Sam brings her audience up to speed on how the current quarantine efforts are impacting American workers, what ER doctors are seeing on the front lines of this pandemic.

title: April 1, 2020
subtitle: April 1, 2020
shortDescription: Sam gets the hang of this 'doing a show from the woods' thing with an episode that's full of the impact coronavirus has had on women, a discussion with Stacey Abrams, and a tune that's the perfect accompaniment to filling out the census.

title: April 8, 2020
subtitle: April 8, 2020
shortDescription: This week, Sam exposes all the shady acts committed by the Trump administration that have been overshadowed by COVID-19, gets a lesson in "legislating from home" from Katie Porter, and opens her wood shed to find musical guest, Jewel!

title: April 15, 2020
subtitle: April 15, 2020
shortDescription: Sam exposes how coronavirus is affecting people of color and then basks in the glow of real leadership that emanates from Sen. Elizabeth Warren. Plus, Author Michael Lewis gives Mike Rubens reasons to regret not stockpiling hand sanitizer.
